Well,
one small step for man,
one giant welt for me.

40:52.617 --> 40:55.950
So, when are you gonna
tell him my Nobel
isn't his to keep?

40:56.037 --> 40:58.198
I don't know.
He saved your ass.
I think he earned it.

40:58.289 --> 41:00.154
No, I earned it.

41:00.249 --> 41:01.500
lt's mine.

41:01.584 --> 41:03.745
Take it away,
lose a great scientist.

41:03.795 --> 41:05.126
It's not
a difficult equation.

41:05.171 --> 41:06.536
You never know,
you might need Thatcher

41:06.631 --> 41:08.838
to dismantle
the next ticking
time bomb.

41:10.301 --> 41:12.041
Good point.

41:13.262 --> 41:14.251
Really?

41:15.974 --> 41:18.465
You did a good job, Carter.
Thanks.

41:21.646 --> 41:23.978
I had a little help
from my crew.

41:25.191 --> 41:27.477
You remember that feeling?

41:28.277 --> 41:29.437
Yeah.

41:30.279 --> 41:32.486
It's nice to know
it can last a lifetime.

41:32.865 --> 41:34.651
And kind of depressing.
A little.

41:34.701 --> 41:36.157
Yeah.
Yeah.

41:37.870 --> 41:40.361
I'm just grateful that
we finally got together.

41:40.456 --> 41:42.868
I said we again, didn't I?
Yeah.

41:43.501 --> 41:45.833
How long is this
supposed to last?

41:48.047 --> 41:50.834
See you tomorrow, Carter.
No, seriously.
